{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 The Range for a task us usually defined in the \cf2 Range From \cf1 and \cf2 Range To\cf1  properties of the Column variables of the Main Table, as illustrated in this example.\par
\par
The\cf2  CndRange() \cf1 function may also be used, for efficiency. This causes Magic to ignore the Range entirely, if the condition for CndRange() is not met. When this task opens and no letter is selected, all the records are automatically shown.\par
\par
Also, when needed, \cf2 Task->Range \cf1 allows any Boolean expression to be used as a Range.\par
